1 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
2 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026)
3 HOUSE JOINT
RESOLUTION 1059 By: Osburn
4
5
6
AS INTRODUCED
7
A Joint Resolution directing the Secretary of State
8 to refer to the people for their approval or
rejection a proposed amendment to Section 1 of
9 Article VI of the Constitution of the State of
Oklahoma; providing ballot title; and directing
10 filing.
11
12 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES AND THE SENATE OF THE
13 2ND SESSION OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE:
14 SECTION 1. The Secretary of State shall refer to the people for
15 their approval or rejection, as and in the manner provided by law,
16 the following proposed amendment to Section 1 of Article VI of the
17 Constitution of the State of Oklahoma to read as follows:
18 Section 1. A. The Executive authority of the state shall be
19 vested in a Governor, Lieutenant Governor, Secretary of State, State
20 Auditor and Inspector, Attorney General, State Treasurer,
21 Superintendent of Public Instruction, Commissioner of Labor,
22 Commissioner of Insurance and other officers provided by law and
23 this Constitution, each of whom shall keep his office and public
24 records, books and papers at the seat of government, and shall
Req. No. 13958 Page 1

1 perf orm such duties as may be designated in this Constitution or
2 prescribed by law.
3 B. The Secretary of State shall be appointed by the Governor by
4 and with the consent of the Senate for a term of four (4) years to
5 run concurrently with the term of the Governor.
6 C. The State Treasurer, Superintendent of Public Instruction,
7 Commissioner of Labor, and Commissioner of Insurance shall be non-
8 partisan officers and shall be elected by non-partisan election in a
9 manner provided by statute.
10 SECTION 2. The Ballot Title for the proposed Constitutional
11 amendment as set forth in SECTION 1 of this resolution shall be in
12 the following form:
13 BALLOT TITLE
14 Legislative Referendum No. ____ State Question No. ____
15 THE GIST OF THE PROPOSITION IS AS FOLLOWS:
16 This measure amends the Oklahoma Constitution in Section 1 of
17 Article 6. The measure makes the offices of the State
18 Treasurer, Superintendent of Public Instruction, Commissioner of
19 Labor, and Commissioner of Insurance non-partisan officers.
20 These officers shall be elected by non-partisan election.
21 SHALL THE PROPOSAL BE APPROVED?
22 FOR THE PROPOSAL — YES _____________
23 AGAINST THE PROPOSAL — NO _____________
24
Req. No. 13958 Page 2

1 SECTION 3. The Chief Clerk of the House of Representatives,
2 immediately after the passage of this act, shall prepare and file
3 one copy thereof, including the Ballot Title set forth in SECTION 2
4 hereof, with the Secretary of State and one copy with the Attorney
5 General.
